  "lastReviewFeedback": "coderabbitai: **Actionable comments posted: 2**\n\n> [!CAUTION]\n> Some comments are outside the diff and can’t be posted inline due to platform limitations.\n> \n> \n> \n> <details>\n> <summary>⚠️ Outside diff range comments (2)</summary><blockquote>\n> \n> <details>\n> <summary>packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-form/hx-form.test.ts (1)</summary><blockquote>\n> \n> `138-154`: _⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟡 Minor_\n> \n> **Use the component-generated wrapper in this passthrough test.**\n> \n> When `action` is set, `hx-form` owns the `<form>` wrapper. Supplying another `<form>` in the fixture means this test can still pass even if the supported render/binding path breaks, because `querySelector('form')` will find the manual form either way.\n> \n> <details>\n> <summary>🧪 Suggested test fixture change</summary>\n> \n> ```diff\n>        const el = await fixture<HelixForm>(`\n>          <hx-form action=\"/api/submit\">\n> -          <form action=\"/api/submit\" method=\"post\">\n> -            <input type=\"text\" name=\"field\" value=\"value\" />\n> -            <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n> -          </form>\n> +          <input type=\"text\" name=\"field\" value=\"value\" />\n> +          <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n>          </hx-form>\n>        `);\n> ```\n> </details>\n> \n> As per coding guidelines, \"No untested code — Every component, utility, and public API must have tests with no exceptions.\"\n> \n> <details>\n> <summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>\n> \n> ```\n> Verify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.\n> \n> In `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-form/hx-form.test.ts` around lines 138\n> - 154, The test currently injects its own <form> inside the <hx-form> fixture\n> which masks the component's own form rendering and binding; update the fixture\n> to only instantiate <hx-form action=\"/api/submit\"></hx-form> (remove the manual\n> <form> markup) so the test exercises the component-generated wrapper (HelixForm\n> rendering). After creating the fixture, wait for t",
